# Platform operator access (customer-safe)

## Two audiences

1. **Company customers** — org members using CRM (pipeline, team, marketing). Sidebar shows their company workspace.
2. **Platform operators** — Connect Intel staff only (`isPlatformAdmin` / `ADMIN_EMAILS` / `invite@connectintel.net`).

Never mix these surfaces. Customers must never land on operator panels or see operator-only errors.

## Operator-only panels

Guard at **three layers** (all required for new operator UI):

1. **Routing** — `frontend/src/lib/platformOperator.js`: `PLATFORM_OPERATOR_PANELS`, `resolvePanelForUser`, `sanitizeAppLocation`. Use in `AppShell` navigate/applyLocation and `resolveInitialAppLocation`.
2. **Component gate** — `PlatformOperatorGate.jsx` for operator panels (`admin-home`, `admin`, `admin-customers`, `integrations`). Redirect or “Go to your workspace”; never raw deny.
3. **API** — `requireAdmin` in `lib/server/auth.js` for `/api/admin/*`.

Adding a new operator panel → add to `PLATFORM_OPERATOR_PANELS` and gate the component.

## Customer-facing copy (never)

Do **not** show customers: `ADMIN_EMAILS`, Vercel, env var names, deployment steps, or “sign in with email listed in…”.

Use neutral copy: “Connect Intel internal area”, “Your workspace account does not include access here”, CTA to **Home / Pipeline / Team**.

## Session / ADMIN_EMAILS

- `isPlatformAdmin` is computed server-side via `isPlatformOperatorUser` + `buildOrgUserResponse` (live `ADMIN_EMAILS`, not JWT-only).
- `GET /api/auth/session` refreshes from DB (`refreshSessionFromDatabase`) and syncs `user.role` from `resolvePlatformRole`.
- After changing `ADMIN_EMAILS` in production: user must **sign out and sign in** (or wait for session refresh).

## Checklist before shipping operator or auth UI

- [ ] Non-operators cannot open panel via URL, history, or persisted session location
- [ ] No infra jargon in any user-visible error or empty state
- [ ] Operator nav (`buildOperatorNavSections`) only when `user.isPlatformAdmin`
